neighbors.name: Westech Components Inc
neighbors.claims: Westech Components Inc is an Arizona-registered corporation [Arizona Corporation Commission](https://ecorp.azcc.gov/CommonHelper/GetFilingDocuments?barcode=00057091) operating as Westech Lumber, which runs a lumber and building materials yard at 8525 N 75th Ave in Peoria [Westech Lumber](https://www.doitbest.com/find-a-store/arizona/5391-westech-lumber-llc/). It is a division of the Younger Brothers Companies, a group supplying large construction contractors with materials and tools across Arizona [Younger Brothers Companies](https://www.youngerbrothers.com/companies/westech). The company’s landholding appears limited to its operational property, indicating it is an active business user rather than a land speculator [Younger Brothers About Us](https://www.youngerbrothers.com/about-us).
neighbors.influence_justification: Established local supplier in construction sector; part of the larger Younger Brothers Companies network.

approach_recommendations.engage: Engage Westech’s management (possibly via Younger Brothers leadership) with assurances the project won’t disrupt their yard operations; emphasize how new development could drive construction demand, benefiting their materials business. Maintain open communication to address any logistical concerns early.

neighbors.profile_summary: Active lumber and building materials supplier affiliated with a major regional construction group.

neighbors.name: 19 Acres LLC
neighbors.claims: 19 Acres LLC is a limited liability company registered in Peoria, Arizona [Bizprofile](https://www.bizprofile.net/az/peoria/azul-pressure-washing-llc). The entity has no visible business operations or public profile and does not appear in standard commercial directories, suggesting it exists solely as a land-holding vehicle [Bizprofile](https://www.bizprofile.net/az/peoria/azul-pressure-washing-llc). No public claims or filings (e.g. zoning cases or liens) were found associated with 19 Acres LLC, indicating its owners have kept a low profile and are likely holding the land for investment or future development.
neighbors.influence_justification: Anonymous land investor with no community presence or political ties.

approach_recommendations.engage: Investigate ownership behind 19 Acres LLC via title records or contacts; if identified, approach discreetly with purchase or partnership options that meet their financial expectations. Emphasize the project’s potential to increase nearby land values to align with their interests.

neighbors.profile_summary: Passive land-holding entity with no operational footprint.

neighbors.name: Peoria (City of)
neighbors.claims: The City of Peoria is the municipal government owning these parcels. The city has demonstrated a strong commitment to sustainability, including the installation of solar covered parking canopies at city facilities and the adoption of a Sustainability Action Plan [City of Peoria News](https://www.peoriaaz.gov/Home/Components/News/News/548/). Peoria’s leadership has a pro-development orientation within the framework of its General Plan 2040, which emphasizes economic prosperity and smart growth [Peoria General Plan](https://www.peoriaaz.gov/government/departments/planning-and-zoning/general-plan). The city actively manages land assets to support community needs and infrastructure [Peoria Sustainability](https://www.peoriaaz.gov/residents/about-peoria/sustainability).
neighbors.influence_justification: Local government authority over zoning and permits; significant sway in public opinion and project approval process.

approach_recommendations.engage: Engage city officials through formal channels early – ensure the project aligns with Peoria’s General Plan 2040 and address any municipal concerns. Highlight public benefits (jobs, tax base) and alignment with the city's existing solar and sustainability initiatives.

neighbors.profile_summary: Municipal entity with documented support for renewable energy and sustainability initiatives.

neighbors.name: Caretaker West Peoria Parcel LLC
neighbors.claims: Caretaker West Peoria Parcel LLC is a registered entity connected to Caretaker Landscape & Tree Management [Bizprofile](https://www.bizprofile.net/az/gilbert/o-side-getaway-llc). The LLC holds real estate associated with Caretaker’s West Valley branch facility at 8737 N 77th Dr in Peoria [Caretaker Landscape Locations](https://www.caretakerlandscape.com/about-us/locations/). Caretaker Landscape is a long-established firm (operating since 1988) led by CEO Matt White, with a focus on sustainable landscape management practices [Caretaker Landscape History](https://www.caretakerlandscape.com/about-us/history/). The company promotes 'Sustainable Landscape Management' (SLM) and water conservation, suggesting alignment with environmentally conscious development [Caretaker Landscape Sustainability](https://www.caretakerlandscape.com/).
neighbors.influence_justification: Well-established local company; moderate political presence but strong stakeholder in immediate area (owns operational facility).

approach_recommendations.engage: Meet with Caretaker Landscape’s leadership (e.g., CEO Matt White) to discuss the project’s timeline and measures to mitigate any construction impacts on their facility. Emphasize opportunities for collaboration and assure that environmental controls will protect their operations.

neighbors.profile_summary: Property holding entity for a major local landscape company with a focus on sustainability.
